[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    21[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;192;197;206mEleven chapter-wide and recipe-specific MEDIUM patterns repeat or are recipe-new (audit-log retention floor with Object Lock specifics including the QHIN's Common Agreement-specified audit-retention floor and the cross-recipe coordination retention floor, three review queues with cohort-and-cycle-aware tooling and the recipe-specific dispute-review queue's cross-QHIN attribution-chain reconstruction discipline plus the governance-evolution queue's multi-disciplinary review with explicit named ownership, threshold calibration governance with privacy-team inclusion and pilot-data infrastructure as separately-governed substrate, idempotency keys per-stage with DLQ topology, cross-recipe event contract with access-control-envelope-aware routing across five consumers, QHIN-credential and signing-key rotation ceremony architectural specification, cross-jurisdictional overlay automation architectural specification, patient-mediated TEFCA flow architectural specification, information-blocking-exception handling pipeline architectural specification, capacity-coordination-across-QHINs architectural specification, cross-QHIN attribution-chain reconstruction operational discipline). Most are explicitly TODO'd or named in the Why-This-Isn't-Production-Ready section; this review carries them forward at MEDIUM severity reflecting the chapter editor's eventual consolidation responsibility.[K
