[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    49[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mLocation:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m AWS Implementation Lambda paragraph: "Each inbound federated query is handled by a Lambda invocation that authenticates the request, validates the exchange-purpose and authorization context, and dispatches to the local matcher. Each outbound federated query is similarly handled by a Lambda that formulates the query, attaches the authorization context, and submits to the QHIN." Architecture diagram shows [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mEB1 -->|FanOut| C5[Recipe 5.5 cross-facility matcher][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m through [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mC9[Internal operational systems][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and shows the QHIN-credential flow [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mSM1[(Secrets Manager QHIN credentials, signing keys)] --> KMS1[(AWS KMS customer-managed keys)][38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m plus [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mHSM1[(AWS CloudHSM high-assurance custody)] --> KMS1[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m. Step 1 [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mhandle_inbound_patient_discovery_query()[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m validates the QHIN's request signature against the QHIN's public-signing-key version, validates the originating-attribution chain, and validates the exchange-purpose claim, but the per-Lambda execution-role binding, the producer-signed envelope schema for cross-recipe events, the dual-control mechanism for the QHIN-credential rotation, and the consumer-side validation for the federation-event fan-out are not specified at the architectural level. The recipe's own TODO at the IAM Permissions row explicitly enumerates the recipe-specific extensions with line-by-line specifications but the architecture text does not actually specify the boundary.[K
