[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    53[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m1[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe inbound-query-handler Lambda accepts QHIN-signed request envelopes carrying the originating-attribution chain, the exchange-purpose claim, and the demographic-feature payload.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Step 1 pseudocode validates the QHIN's request signature against the QHIN's public-signing-key version (with the previous version included during rotation), validates the attribution chain against the participant-authorized-QHINs list, and validates the exchange-purpose claim. But the per-Lambda execution-role binding, the producer-signed envelope schema, and the rejection semantics for misconfigured QHIN-credential rotations are not specified at the architectural level. A misconfigured rotation (the participant's QHIN-key store falls behind the QHIN's actual rotation cadence; the previous-version inclusion window expires before the QHIN's actual cutover; the participant accepts a request signed under a key that has been deprecated by the QHIN's framework) silently produces wrong-record disclosures with audit-trail attribution to a QHIN that is not the actual originator.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    54[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    55[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m2[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe outbound-query-formulator Lambda formulates a request envelope signed under the participant's signing credential.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The Step 4 pseudocode signs the query under the participant's signing credential loaded from Secrets Manager. The signing credential's per-rotation Secrets Manager secret is named in the recipe text, but the architecture does not specify the producer-signed envelope's schema, the per-Lambda execution-role binding, the rotation cadence enforcement, or the audit-attribution discipline for the credential-version active at signing time. A forged outbound query (an attacker who has compromised the outbound-query-formulator Lambda's execution role and can sign queries under the participant's credential) silently produces queries that the federation routes under the participant's identity to participants whose responses will be returned to the attacker's downstream consumer.[K
