[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    61[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m5[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe QHIN-credential rotation is the most consequential single event in the entire pipeline.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The QHIN-credential is the federation-trust-anchor; if the credential is compromised, the participant's federation participation is operationally suspended (the QHIN can revoke the credential under the framework's governance) or, worse, the credential is silently substituted with a credential the attacker controls and the participant's queries are signed under the attacker's identity for the period before detection. The recipe correctly elevates the rotation as a coordinated event with dual-control approval, but the architecture does not specify the dual-control mechanism, the inter-organizational binding (two operators from non-overlapping organizational units is the correct policy; the architecture should enforce it through cross-account approval), the audit-log replication SLA before the rotation completes, the catch-up-window's specific access-control-constraint, or the post-rotation operational-verification SLA.[K
