[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    65[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m7[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe cross-recipe EventBridge fan-out reaches recipes 5.5, 5.6, 5.7, 5.8, and per-participant operational systems.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The architecture diagram shows the fan-out but the architecture text does not specify the producer-signed envelope on the event payload, the consumer-side validation of the asserted source, the schema-version-pinning policy, or the access-control-envelope-aware routing. A forged [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtefca_query_completed[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m event could feed false data into recipe 5.5's cross-facility matcher (producing wrong-cross-organizational identity assertions), into recipe 5.6's claims-clinical linkage (producing wrong-claims-to-clinical attribution), into recipe 5.7's longitudinal-name-change pipeline (producing wrong-historical-name reasoning), into recipe 5.8's PPRL pipeline (producing wrong-encoded-record linkages), or into the per-participant operational systems (producing wrong-operational-state).[K
