[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    67[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106m8[38;2;191;97;106m.[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe federation-event producers feed the dispute queue and the governance-evolution queue from recipe-external sources.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The dispute queue receives incoming and outgoing disputes from cross-QHIN coordination; the governance-evolution queue receives Common Agreement updates, QTF updates, QHIN-framework updates, and jurisdictional-overlay-rule updates. Each is a recipe-external producer; the queue handlers have no specified mechanism to validate that the asserted [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mevent.source[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m matches the actual originating principal. A forged [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtefca_dispute_raised[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m event with attacker-controlled [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdispute_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m and [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mattribution_chain[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m could mass-suppress legitimate matches under the dispute-resolution playbook; a forged [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtefca_governance_event_received[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m event could silently change the participant's overlay-rule configuration without the regulatory-monitoring function's review; a forged [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mtefca_credential_rotated[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m event could trigger an unauthorized rotation that loses the participant's federation participation.[K
