[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    69[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;191;97;106mThe HIPAA Privacy Rule's minimum-necessary requirement, the Common Agreement's authentication-and-authorization framework, the QHIN's framework's audit-and-attribution requirements, and the federation-trust-anchor integrity all depend on the identity boundary. A read of the cross-network query handler that bypasses the QHIN-signature validation is a minimum-necessary violation and a Common Agreement breach. A QHIN-credential rotation that succeeds without dual-control approval is a uniquely consequential failure mode that no prior recipe in the chapter has at this severity. A patient-mediated cross-network query that succeeds with forged patient authentication is a patient-impersonation attack that the institution cannot detect. A forged cross-recipe event could cascade through five downstream recipes and the per-participant operational systems with no mechanism to detect or recover.[K
