[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    201[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m  [38;2;180;142;173m*[38;2;180;142;173m"Cohort-stratified accuracy monitoring uses the cohort-axis-hash labels from each participant rather than the underlying axis values; the cohort-axis-hashes are non-reversible by construction. Recipe-specific cohort axes (inherited from 5.7 and 5.8 plus federation-specific extensions): geographic-region cohort hash; age-decade cohort hash; sex-or-gender cohort hash, populated only from patient-consented self-identification at each participant; name-tradition cohort hash; jurisdictional-overlay cohort hash (post-Dobbs reproductive-health-care state-law overlay applicable, 42 CFR Part 2 substance-use-treatment-record applicable, gender-affirming-care state-law overlay applicable, HIV-and-genetic-information state-specific rule applicable, juvenile-record state-specific rule applicable, none-applicable); responder-quality-tier cohort hash (high / medium / low based on the per-responder match-quality monitoring); patient-consent-for-fairness-monitoring cohort hash (fairness-monitoring opt-in versus opt-out); cross-jurisdictional-overlay cohort hash. Metrics: (a) per-cohort cross-network match rate (computed weekly); (b) per-cohort false-acceptance rate (sampled audit, computed weekly); (c) per-cohort response-window-completeness (computed weekly); (d) per-cohort review-queue aging (computed weekly); (e) per-cohort sampled error rate (computed monthly). Disparity calculation: absolute difference between the cohort with the highest rate and the cohort with the lowest rate, computed per-metric per-cycle. Alarm thresholds: match-rate disparity > 0.10 = MEDIUM; review-queue-aging disparity > 0.05 = MEDIUM; false-acceptance-rate disparity > 0.02 = HIGH (because false acceptances at federation scale produce wrong-record disclosures that the originating participant cannot retract from the consumer); response-window-completeness disparity > 0.10 = HIGH; any disparity > 2x the threshold = HIGH. Alarms route to the analytics governance committee, the equity-monitoring committee, the privacy team (which has explicit federation-equity-evaluation authority for this recipe), the institutional governance committee for cross-jurisdictional overlays (for cross-jurisdictional-overlay-affected cohorts), and the federation-participation steering committee (which has explicit framework-compliance-evaluation authority for this recipe), with a 5-business-day SLA for the first investigation report. The post-mortem and any remediation (per-cohort tolerance tuning, per-cohort feature weighting, per-cohort reference-data gap analysis, per-responder-quality-tier escalation through the QHIN coordination layer) is documented in the cohort-disparity ledger and reviewed quarterly by the federation-participation steering committee with privacy-team co-chair. The dual-interpretation translation is explicit: cohort-disparity metrics in this recipe are simultaneously fairness signals and framework-compliance signals; cohorts with anomalously low cross-network match rates may be silently dropped at scale (information-blocking-compliance signal: the participant whose queries are silently dropped at scale can face an enforcement action); cohorts with anomalously high false-acceptance rates may be producing wrong-record disclosures at scale (Common-Agreement accuracy-expectation signal: the participant's responses that the consumer cannot retract may breach the framework's accuracy expectations). The privacy team's federation-equity-evaluation and the federation-participation steering committee's framework-compliance-evaluation are the authoritative determinations on whether a cohort-disparity event requires framework-engagement (escalation to the QHIN coordination layer, dispute-resolution intake, framework-governance review) in addition to local-tolerance-tuning."[38;2;180;142;173m*[K
